we define rules in lisioners http or https right?

Yes, exactly! Rules are defined inside Listeners:

ALB
├── Listener (HTTP :80)
│   ├── Rule 1: /api    → api-service
│   ├── Rule 2: /auth   → auth-service
│   └── Rule 3: default → 404
│
└── Listener (HTTPS :443)
    ├── Rule 1: /api    → api-service
    ├── Rule 2: /auth   → auth-service
    └── Rule 3: default → 404

So 100 rules limit is per ALB (across all listeners):

HTTP  listener → 50 rules
HTTPS listener → 50 rules
Total          → 100 rules per ALB ✅

In AWS Console:

ALB
→ Listeners tab
→ Click HTTP:80 or HTTPS:443
→ View/Edit Rules
→ Add rules here ✅
